						               													<description>In The End: Faith in Humanity is a post apocalyptic survival game. It is story driven not combat driven. The Characters you have to choose from are varied with their own stories.&amp;#10;In The End is a 1-6 player, 3 board game. It has ten unique bosses to fight and many events to overcome.&amp;#10;The play mechanics are simple roll a d6, move up to that number. If you land in a square with Character, Event, or Item you pull that card and resolve the card. On each board the player must complete 3 Character Cards to reveal the boss. Once the boss is revealed you must move to that square and fight the boss. &amp;#10;This is done over all three boards. In solo play you undertake this great journey alone. When playing in a party you all must fight the boss together. In Versus mode you are in a race to beat the three bosses. &amp;#10;After defeating the third boss you find and are granted access to Sanctuary, a city where civilization is being rebuilt. You lose by dying or in Versus by not making it to Sanctuary first.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
